\par {\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 An experimental client/server mode of operation is also available. }
\par {\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The script /opt/apogee/scripts/startserver will lauch a camera server process which listens on port 2001 for connections. Commands can be sent from any other computer by copying the script /opt/apogee/scripts/apogeeclient to the remote machine and editing 
it to reflect}
\par {\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 the location of the machine hosting the camera.  The client machine must have tcl installed  (in /usr/bin/tclsh).}
\par 
\par {\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The socket interface is very simple and could easily be driven by user programs written in any standard programming language.}
\par 
